results.name: Number of non-isomorphic multiset partitions of weight n with no constant parts and only two distinct vertices.
comment: First differs from A304967 at a(10) = 50, A304967(10) = 49.
The weight of a multiset partition is the sum of sizes of its parts. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
Also the number of positive integer matrices with only two columns and sum of entries equal to n, up to row and column permutations.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
